body:
@cammellos curious to hear your thoughts on this as well, especially re: how do we decide which chain IDs to attach to a community membership request, given that multiple chain ID configurations would yield proof of enough funds to fulfill token permission requirements.

@jrainville as for migration/backwards compatibility:

I even tend to go with option 1). If we have a Status version in the near future that only performs these optimized membership requests, then future communities will all end up in that code path (where checking all chains is only done when there's no chain ID info to check for).

If the argument is that we don't want that, because for our Status community specifically that'd mean owner nodes will always check all chains, then I'd argue that we might as well create a new community that Status-CC need to request access to.

If we go with option 2), they'd be kicked and need to sent a request again anyways.

Only thing that just comes into my mind is that the entire discord / archive story will have to be redone as well (which we probably don't want). So that'd be a strong argument to keep the current Status community and find a backwards compatible path forward (or migration).
